  "instructions": [
    "Heat the sesame oil in a large pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.",
    "Add the long beans and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together the soy sauce, brown sugar, and crushed red pepper. Pour the mixture over the long beans and stir to combine.",
    "Add the water to the pan and bring to a boil. Then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.",
    "Season the long beans with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Wrap the long beans in pandan leaves and roast in a robata grill or oven at 400F for 10-15 minutes, or until the leaves are crispy and the beans are tender.",
    "Sprinkle the toasted sesame seeds over the top of the long beans and serve hot.",
    "Garnish with additional tahini and sesame seeds if desired.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
  ],
